<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF386A87F82095B71677BF39" bold="true" box="[2012,2167,1006,1035]" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F77095B716CFBF01" authority="Kruskop &amp; Borisenko, 2013" authorityName="Kruskop &amp; Borisenko" authorityYear="2013" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annatessae">Myotis annatessae Kruskop &amp; Borisenko, 2013</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="74FC3CA3FF386A87F711924316F4BFB0" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3783319416" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">
“Song Con river valley, Saola Basecamp, Vu Quang, 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF386A87F64F92181658BFB0" country="Vietnam" name="Ha Tinh" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">Ha Tinh Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF386A87F79B923C16E5BFB0" box="[2151,2277,1125,1154]" name="Vietnam" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.”
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF386A87F82092D11713BD3E" blockId="195.[2011,2608,1006,1430]" lastBlockId="195.[1398,2608,1437,2656]" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F78992D11750BF9B" authority="Kaup, 1829" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[2165,2384,1160,1193]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" species="muricola">Myotis; muricola</taxonomicName>
species group. See 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F7E692F6167ABFE2" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[2074,2170,1199,1232]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="959" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">M. ater</taxonomicName>
. This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F7F3928E16BEBFCA" authority="Kruskop et al., 2018" authorityName="Kruskop" authorityYear="2018" box="[2063,2238,1239,1272]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ancricola">M. ancricola</taxonomicName>
, but their relationships with other 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F78792A716CFBE2D" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[2171,2255,1278,1311]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
are still unclear; limited genetic data suggest a possible link with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F821930F169FBE5D" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1874" box="[2013,2207,1366,1391]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">M. montivagus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F74C930F1760BE5D" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2224,2400,1366,1391]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">M. annectans</taxonomicName>
, and M. rosset, whereas earlier studies found 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F66D932C1B9EBE8C" authorityName="Kruskop &amp; Borisenko" authorityYear="2013" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annatessae">M. annatessae</taxonomicName>
to be close to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F97C93C41923BE8C" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1664,1827,1437,1470]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
. Populations of 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF386A87F7EA93C4166ABE8C" box="[2070,2154,1437,1470]" name="China" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">China</collectingCountry>
show genetic differences from those of 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF386A87FA0E939D1832BED7" box="[1522,1586,1476,1509]" name="Laos" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">Laos</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF386A87F986939D18F4BED7" box="[1658,1780,1476,1509]" name="Vietnam" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, and may be taxonomically separable. Six specimens from West Bengal were previously attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F83493B21667BD3E" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[1992,2151,1515,1548]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
